          <m>y=\sqrt{1-x^2}</m> on <m>[-1,1]</m> about the <m>x</m>-axis.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>2\pi\int_0^1 \sqrt{1-x^2}\sqrt{1+x/(1-x^2)}\, dx = 4\pi</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
